# Documentation maintenance

On **any** code change in this repo, update relevant docs in the **same PR/commit**. Never leave module status tables stale.

## Single source of truth

`docs/AGENTS.md` is the primary agent onboarding guide. Keep its module table and repository map accurate.

## What to update

| Change type | Files to update |
|-------------|-----------------|
| New or completed feature module | `docs/AGENTS.md` module table · `README.md` § Implemented Modules · navigation notes if routes changed |
| New navigation route / wiring | `docs/AGENTS.md` module table · `README.md` § Navigation |
| New top-level dir or package | `docs/AGENTS.md` repository map |
| Sync engine (handlers, queue, workers) | `docs/SYNC_ENGINE.md` · `docs/AGENTS.md` if handler registry changes |
| Architecture / layer boundaries | `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` · cross-check `docs/AGENTS.md` invariants |
| Build, SDK, API URL, branch info | `README.md` Quick Reference |
| New doc file | `README.md` Documentation section · link from `docs/AGENTS.md` |

## Minimum checklist before finishing a task

1. Did module status (✅ / 🔶 / ❌) change? → Update `docs/AGENTS.md` + `README.md`.
2. Did sync behavior change? → Update `docs/SYNC_ENGINE.md`.
3. Did you add user-facing strings? → Both `values/strings.xml` and `values-te/strings.xml` (not docs, but required).
4. Did you add a new package? → `docs/AGENTS.md` repository map.

## Do not

- Ship feature work without updating the module status table.
- Duplicate long architecture prose in commits — edit the canonical doc file instead.
- Let `README.md` and `docs/AGENTS.md` module tables diverge.
